        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1961-01-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1961-01-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="60"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d60">
                <head>60. Central Intelligence Agency Information Report<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d60fn1">Source: Central Intelligence Agency Files, Job 79–00149A,
                            <gloss target="#t_DDOIMS_1">DDO/IMS</gloss> Files, African Division,
                        Senate Select Committee, Volume III, Box 23, Folder 2. Confidential; Noforn;
                        Continued Control.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1961-01-18">January 18, 1961</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>TDCS–3/462, 691, Field Report [<hi rend="italic">text not declassified</hi>]</p>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Arrival of <persName corresp="#p_LPE_1">Patrice Lumumba</persName> in
                        Elisabethville</item>
                </list>
                <p>1. <persName corresp="#p_LPE_1">Patrice Lumumba</persName> arrived about 1700
                    hours 17 Jan via air Congo DC–4 from Moana (near Matadi). His arrival was not
                    expected by <gloss target="#t_GOK_1">GOK</gloss>
                    <pb facs="0113" n="80" xml:id="pg_80"/> and plane had to circle for one hour
                    while security forces were assembled to meet aircraft. <persName
                        corresp="#p_LPE_1">Lumumba</persName> and two fellow detainees debarked
                    chained together and showing signs of having been badly beaten in flight. All
                        <persName corresp="#p_LPE_1">Lumumba</persName> teeth have been knocked out
                    beaten after disembarked but not too roughly, then removed unknown prison ([<hi
                        rend="italic">less than 1 line not declassified</hi>] Comment: One source
                    claimed <persName corresp="#p_LPE_1">Lumumba</persName> in Jadotville but the
                    other believed Jadotville too insecure and he probably taken somewhere like
                    Sandoa). 2. Field dissem: State.</p>
                <p>End of message.</p>
            </div>
